, "mention": "kisspeptin", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.8517544865608215, "span": {"begin": 671, "end": 681}}, {"id": ["mesh:D004967"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "estrogen", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.999665379524231, "span": {"begin": 719, "end": 727}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2099"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "estrogen receptors", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9830711483955383, "span": {"begin": 719, "end": 737}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2099"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ER&alpha", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9596533179283142, "span": {"begin": 752, "end": 760}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3814"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "Kisspeptin", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9769418835639954, "span": {"begin": 764, "end": 774}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3814"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "kisspeptin hormone", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9614232778549194, "span": {"begin": 883, "end": 901}}, {"id": ["mesh:D004967"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "estrogen", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9993426203727722, "span": {"begin": 943, "end": 951}}, {"id": ["mesh:D004967"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Estrogen", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9974853992462158, "span": {"begin": 963, "end": 971}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2099"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "Estrogen Receptor Alpha", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9979414343833923, "span": {"begin": 963, "end": 986}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2099"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ERa)", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9943958520889282, "span": {"begin": 988, "end": 992}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "neurons", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.6455885171890259, "span": {"begin": 1006, "end": 1013}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3814"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "kisspeptin hormone", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9794777035713196, "span": {"begin": 1124, "end": 1142}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:26284"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "ERa receptor", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9892138242721558, "span": {"begin": 1164, "end": 1176}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "neurons", "obj": "cell_type", "prob": 0.6994643807411194, "span": {"begin": 1195, "end": 1202}}, {"id": ["CUI-less"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "arcuate", "obj": "DNA", "prob": 0.9384769201278687, "span": {"begin": 1212, "end": 1219}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:2099"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "ERa", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.9793577194213867, "span": {"begin": 1315, "end": 1318}}, {"id": ["NCBIGene:3814"], "is_neural_normalized": true, "mention": "kisspeptin", "obj": "gene", "prob": 0.986631453037262, "span": {"begin": 1338, "end": 1348}}], "text": "Estrogen receptor alpha (ER&alpha;) is a nuclear receptor that can be activated by estrogens, a group of hormones involved in reproductive development. Activation of ER&alpha; promotes the transcription and regulation of physiological processes involved with the endocrine system(Christian and Moenter, 2007). Kisspeptins are a family of peptide hormones with varying amino acid lengths derived from the KISS1 gene &amp; neurons (Nejad et al., 2017). Breakthrough research in the 2000s has shown that kisspeptins play a large role in the hypothalamic-pituitary-gonadal axis with gonadotropin circulation(Alcin et al., 2013). In particular, more recent research has shown kisspeptin neurons contain large populations of estrogen receptors, particularly ER&alpha;.  Kisspeptin is a key signalling neuropeptide hormone in mammals and some other vertebrates. &nbsp;Positive feedback for kisspeptin hormone production is due to increased levels of estrogen binding to Estrogen Receptor Alpha (ERa) receptors in neurons from the anteroventral periventricular nucleus (AVPV) region of the hypothalamus, while negative feedback for kisspeptin hormone production is due to ERa receptor activation of the neurons from the arcuate nucleus (ARC) region of the hypothalamus (Uenoyama et al. 2021). &nbsp;Increased activation of ERa leads to increased kisspeptin in the AVPV region.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:45:48 +0000 2026"}